This paper involves analyzing large-scale consumption data and evaluating algorithms for predicting food consumption behavior. This suggests that it could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
